'''HMS ''Curlew''''' was an 18-gun [[brig-sloop]] of the [[Royal Navy]], commissioned in June 1795 under Commander Francis Ventris Field for Admiral [[Adam Duncan, 1st Viscount Duncan|Duncan's]] fleet.
On 31 October 1796 she disappeared during a storm in the North Sea, and was presumed to have foundered with all hands.<ref name=Winfield/><ref>Grocott (1997), p.39.</ref>
