{{Taxobox | image = Eoph_MagelaT_site2.jpg | image_caption = ''[[Eophreatoicus]]'', a freshwater isopod from [[Kakadu National Park]], [[Australia]] | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Arthropod]]a | subphylum = [[Crustacean|Crustacea]] | classis = [[Malacostraca]] | ordo = [[Isopoda]] | subordo = [[Phreatoicidea]] | familia = '''Phreatoicidae''' | familia_authority = [[Charles Chilton (zoologist)|Chilton]], 1891&nbsp;<ref>{{ITIS |id=541912 |taxon=Phreatoicidae}}</ref> }}
'''Phreatoicidae''' is a [[family (biology)|family]] of blind, [[freshwater]] [[isopod]]s. They have survived apparently unchanged for 350 million years, and are only found in [[South Africa]], [[India]], [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]]. They were first found near [[Christchurch]] in 1882 by [[Charles Chilton (zoologist)|Charles Chilton]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.niwa.co.nz/news-and-publications/news/all/ancient-creatures-re-discovered-thriving-in-southern-new-zealand |title=Ancient creatures re-discovered thriving in southern New Zealand |date=October 2009 |publisher=[[National Institute of Water and Atmospheric Research|NIWA]] |accessdate=April 11, 2010}}</ref> The family Phreatoicidae now contains 13 genera:<ref>{{cite web |author=Marilyn Schotte |year=2009 |title=Phreatoicidae |editor1=M. Schotte |editor2=C. B. Boyko |editor3=N. L. Bruce |editor4=G. C. B. Poore |editor5=S. Taiti |editor6=G. D. F. Wilson |work=World Marine, Freshwater and Terrestrial Isopod Crustaceans database |publisher=[[World Register of Marine Species]] |url=http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=249332 |accessdate=April 11, 2010}}</ref> {{div col|colwidth=20em}} *''[[Colacanthotelson]]'' <small>Nicholls, 1944</small> *''[[Colubotelson]]'' <small>Nicholls, 1944</small> *''[[Crenoicus]]'' <small>Nicholls, 1944</small> *''[[Gariwerdeus]]'' <small>Wilson & Keable, 2002</small> *''[[Mesacanthotelson]]'' <small>Nicholls, 1944</small> *''[[Metaphreatoicus]]'' <small>Nicholls, 1944</small> *''[[Naiopegia]]'' <small>Wilson & Keable, 2002</small> *''[[Neophreatoicus]]'' <small>Nicholls, 1944</small> *''[[Notamphisopus]]'' <small>Nicholls, 1944</small> *''[[Onchotelson]]'' <small>Nicholls, 1944</small> *''[[Paraphreatoicus]]'' <small>Nicholls, 1944</small> *''[[Phreatoicus]]'' <small>Chilton, 1883</small> *''[[Uramphisopus]]'' <small>Nicholls, 1943</small> {{div col end}}
